div.p:
The Order in Council of the 24 September 1860 (copy enclosed



      Copy of order on p. 392.
) directs that where an officer shall fail for one month or upwards to furnish the security required of him, payment of his salary shall be withheld until this has been done, and I am now to state that it is necessary that the Order in Council shall be strictly enforced in future, and that the Treasurer will look to you to give effect to it as far as the officers in the Department of which you are the Permanent Head are concerned.
